1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:05,588
[brazen music playing]

2
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:20,395
PREVIOUSLY

3
00:00:20,478 --> 00:00:22,564
Please help me. They abducted Ponyo.

4
00:00:22,647 --> 00:00:25,150
- [Ponyo] Where are you taking me?!
- Shut up!

5
00:00:25,233 --> 00:00:26,484
[gunshot]

6
00:00:26,568 --> 00:00:28,486
- Shoot him!
- [Ponyo] Atoy!

7
00:00:29,195 --> 00:00:30,238
[screams]

8
00:00:31,573 --> 00:00:33,783
[Atoy] <i>By authority</i>
<i>of the Antiterrorism Council</i>

9
00:00:33,867 --> 00:00:36,244
<i>of the Philippines, you will be detained.</i>

10
00:00:36,327 --> 00:00:39,956
We have evidence linking you to financing
some terrorist groups in South East Asia.

11
00:00:40,040 --> 00:00:42,000
You'll really go to hell first.

12
00:00:45,462 --> 00:00:46,796
[Mercado, in English] <i>Good job, Padua.</i>

13
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:50,133
Merelli is currently
being transferred to the camp.

14
00:00:51,134 --> 00:00:52,594
[Atoy] <i>Where's Elaine?</i>

15
00:00:52,677 --> 00:00:54,929
- [Karla] <i>Atoy!</i>
- [Paldo] <i>You literally just got home.</i>

16
00:00:55,013 --> 00:00:56,598
Stay out of this, bro!

17
00:00:56,681 --> 00:00:58,641
[crowd clamoring]

18
00:01:02,479 --> 00:01:05,398
- [Delfin] <i>Are you sure it's Atoy?</i>
- Yes, he's returned already.

19
00:01:05,482 --> 00:01:06,316
That's enough!

20
00:01:06,399 --> 00:01:07,942
[Delfin] <i>You were gone for years.</i>

21
00:01:08,526 --> 00:01:10,695
And now, you've come back
just to stir things up?

22
00:01:10,779 --> 00:01:12,155
[Cita] <i>This is your home.</i>

23
00:01:13,239 --> 00:01:15,366
<i>Your parents raised you here.</i>

24
00:01:15,450 --> 00:01:16,826
SIR DELFIN'S
TAILORING SHOP

25
00:01:16,910 --> 00:01:22,040
[music concludes]

26
00:01:22,123 --> 00:01:23,500
[Cita] Eat first.

27
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:26,503
Atoy, thank you
for all the thoughtful gifts

28
00:01:26,586 --> 00:01:31,674
you’ve sent me and Karla
every Christmas and on our birthdays.

29
00:01:32,383 --> 00:01:33,760
[Atoy] Don't mention it. Anything for you.

30
00:01:33,843 --> 00:01:35,678
That’s my way of saying thank you.

31
00:01:35,762 --> 00:01:37,806
You’ve been working here for a long time,
and I truly appreciate it.

32
00:01:37,889 --> 00:01:40,391
Whenever your father hears
that you’ve sent gifts,

33
00:01:40,475 --> 00:01:44,771
he always asks if you will be coming home
for Christmas or New Year,

34
00:01:44,854 --> 00:01:46,481
or even his birthday.

35
00:01:46,564 --> 00:01:47,732
He shouldn't have bothered.

36
00:01:47,816 --> 00:01:49,734
He knows very well that's impossible.

37
00:01:49,818 --> 00:01:52,737
You can't blame him for hoping.
[clicks tongue]

38
00:01:52,821 --> 00:01:54,572
Also, it’s a good thing you’re here.

39
00:01:54,656 --> 00:01:58,201
Your father’s starting
to show signs of aging.

40
00:01:58,284 --> 00:02:00,995
He’s been having headaches
and frequent bouts of vertigo.

41
00:02:01,079 --> 00:02:01,913
[inhales]

42
00:02:01,996 --> 00:02:05,458
I think you should convince him
to visit a doctor.

43
00:02:05,542 --> 00:02:07,168
It’s no surprise his health is suffering.

44
00:02:07,252 --> 00:02:09,295
Just look at the conditions he works in.

45
00:02:09,796 --> 00:02:12,298
It's only a matter of time
before this place falls apart.

46
00:02:12,382 --> 00:02:13,716
That's an exaggeration!

47
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:16,427
This place has definitely
survived the test of time.

48
00:02:16,511 --> 00:02:18,847
- [chuckles]
- Anyway, drink up.

49
00:02:18,930 --> 00:02:20,098
Thank you.

50
00:02:20,181 --> 00:02:22,600
[gentle music playing]

51
00:02:22,684 --> 00:02:23,893
Aah!

52
00:02:25,061 --> 00:02:26,229
I better go get some rest now.

53
00:02:26,312 --> 00:02:27,397
- Ah--
- Thank you.

54
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:28,982
Don't mention it.
Anyway, let me accompany you.

55
00:02:29,065 --> 00:02:30,483
I'm sure your room is a mess.

56
00:02:30,567 --> 00:02:33,069
- I'll clean it up for you.
- Oh, no need-- [clicks tongue]

57
00:02:33,153 --> 00:02:35,155
- Let me do this for you.
- No, you're not our househelp.

58
00:02:35,238 --> 00:02:36,156
- I insist.
- Come on.

59
00:02:36,239 --> 00:02:37,407
I'll go get the broom.

60
00:02:38,158 --> 00:02:40,201
Just let me do this. Let me get the broom.

61
00:02:40,285 --> 00:02:41,202
[gasps]

62
00:02:42,036 --> 00:02:48,167
[gentle music continues]

63
00:02:52,547 --> 00:02:58,177
[gentle music concludes]

64
00:03:05,852 --> 00:03:07,520
[sentimental music playing]

65
00:03:07,604 --> 00:03:12,859
Wow, who would've thought that
Delfin has always kept your room tidy?

66
00:03:28,708 --> 00:03:32,462
[sentimental music continues]

67
00:03:32,545 --> 00:03:34,255
Anyway, I'll go ahead now.

68
00:03:39,385 --> 00:03:46,267
[sentimental music continues]

69
00:04:12,669 --> 00:04:16,756
[sentimental music]

70
00:04:16,839 --> 00:04:20,218
[Atoy] Your husband is something else.

71
00:04:20,301 --> 00:04:25,932
He keeps my room tidy, yet he can’t
even take care of your grave.

72
00:04:26,015 --> 00:04:27,267
My goodness.

73
00:04:27,350 --> 00:04:32,272
Mom, I’m sorry it’s been
so long since I last visited.

74
00:04:32,355 --> 00:04:36,067
[Atoy] <i>A lot has happened</i>
<i>since I was last here.</i>

75
00:04:36,150 --> 00:04:38,611
<i>Did you know I joined the army?</i>

76
00:04:39,195 --> 00:04:40,571
<i>I couldn’t tell you before</i>

77
00:04:40,655 --> 00:04:44,284
<i>because I knew you’d never allow it</i>
<i>and you’d be furious with me.</i>

78
00:04:44,367 --> 00:04:50,206
But Mom, did you know I learned so much
and met so many people?

79
00:04:50,290 --> 00:04:52,625
Actually, there’s one person I met…

80
00:04:53,751 --> 00:04:54,752
[scoffs]

81
00:04:55,837 --> 00:04:57,880
…who reminds me so much of you.

82
00:05:02,051 --> 00:05:06,681
[light music playing]

83
00:05:19,485 --> 00:05:20,486
My dear,

84
00:05:22,780 --> 00:05:24,365
when I’m gone…

85
00:05:26,409 --> 00:05:27,243
[sniffs]

86
00:05:27,327 --> 00:05:30,747
…I will become
a butterfly too, just like that.

87
00:05:30,830 --> 00:05:32,665
[sobs] So if…

88
00:05:33,166 --> 00:05:38,212
you start to miss me, or feel sad…

89
00:05:38,296 --> 00:05:39,839
[sobbing]

90
00:05:40,715 --> 00:05:42,925
…I'll show myself to you.

91
00:05:43,009 --> 00:05:43,885
Hmm?

92
00:05:43,968 --> 00:05:48,806
So you'll see that, in the end,
everything will be okay.

93
00:05:49,307 --> 00:05:50,266
[sniffs] Okay?

94
00:05:50,850 --> 00:05:53,186
[soft sob]

95
00:05:53,269 --> 00:05:54,353
Got it?

96
00:05:54,854 --> 00:05:56,147
[sniffs]

97
00:05:56,230 --> 00:05:57,774
I love you so much.

98
00:05:57,857 --> 00:05:59,150
[soft chuckle]

99
00:05:59,859 --> 00:06:06,157
[sobbing]

100
00:06:06,240 --> 00:06:10,036
[sentimental music continues]

101
00:06:17,794 --> 00:06:18,753
[Atoy] <i>To be honest,</i>

102
00:06:18,836 --> 00:06:20,880
<i>that person is the one</i>
<i>who convinced me to go home</i>

103
00:06:21,964 --> 00:06:23,257
<i>and try to talk to Dad.</i>

104
00:06:25,468 --> 00:06:27,512
[melancholic music playing]

105
00:06:28,930 --> 00:06:29,972
Mom,

106
00:06:31,766 --> 00:06:37,021
please help me.
I don’t even know how to face him.

107
00:06:38,064 --> 00:06:41,818
It feels like I don't know him anymore.

108
00:06:42,401 --> 00:06:44,237
Mom, please, guide me.

109
00:06:44,946 --> 00:06:46,572
[music concludes]

110
00:06:48,074 --> 00:06:51,577
[suave music playing]

111
00:06:51,661 --> 00:06:53,412
FATHER'S LANE
FOOD HUB IN BACLARAN

112
00:06:53,496 --> 00:06:55,331
[music continues]

113
00:06:56,958 --> 00:06:58,084
[swishing]

114
00:07:05,550 --> 00:07:09,720
[ripping]

115
00:07:28,322 --> 00:07:32,535
[music concludes]

116
00:07:40,793 --> 00:07:41,669
[Emerson] Hi.

117
00:07:42,879 --> 00:07:45,548
Goodness, Emerson! What took you so long?

118
00:07:45,631 --> 00:07:48,134
It is my day off today.

119
00:07:48,759 --> 00:07:50,928
I'm really sorry! I got caught in traffic.

120
00:07:51,012 --> 00:07:52,972
Anyway, here it is.
I'll leave this right here.

121
00:07:53,556 --> 00:07:55,349
- Okay.
- Yes, it's already 6:00 p.m.

122
00:07:55,850 --> 00:07:56,767
I better get going now.

123
00:07:57,685 --> 00:07:58,811
I need to go.

124
00:07:59,520 --> 00:08:00,354
Okay.

125
00:08:00,855 --> 00:08:02,023
See you soon!

126
00:08:02,565 --> 00:08:06,861
SIR DELFIN'S
TAILORING SHOP

127
00:08:06,944 --> 00:08:08,029
Huh…

128
00:08:08,112 --> 00:08:09,697
Sir, do you want to avail of our services?

129
00:08:09,780 --> 00:08:11,365
The shop's already closed.

130
00:08:11,949 --> 00:08:13,159
You should come back some other time.

131
00:08:13,242 --> 00:08:14,410
What exactly do you need?

132
00:08:14,494 --> 00:08:15,328
A suit?

133
00:08:15,411 --> 00:08:18,080
Something for a wedding
or an awards night?

134
00:08:18,581 --> 00:08:20,208
- [scoffs]
- Uh…

135
00:08:21,250 --> 00:08:24,587
Sir, if you want, you should use
my service instead.

136
00:08:24,670 --> 00:08:26,839
It’s 5,000 pesos less
than what Sir Delfin charges!

137
00:08:26,923 --> 00:08:28,508
[mischievous music playing]

138
00:08:28,591 --> 00:08:30,176
- Really?
- Yes!

139
00:08:30,259 --> 00:08:35,431
He’s alreay old.
He is a master cutter, but…

140
00:08:35,515 --> 00:08:36,641
yet he still messes up.

141
00:08:36,724 --> 00:08:38,684
As for me, I’m an expert.

142
00:08:38,768 --> 00:08:41,812
I’ve been doing this for years,
and I am now expert in this job.

143
00:08:41,896 --> 00:08:44,482
In fact, I plan to take over
this business once the old man is gone.

144
00:08:44,565 --> 00:08:45,650
Is that so?

145
00:08:45,733 --> 00:08:46,776
- Yes.
- Oh…

146
00:08:46,859 --> 00:08:48,903
Does he have children?

147
00:08:48,986 --> 00:08:50,821
Well, he never mentioned them.

148
00:08:51,864 --> 00:08:54,492
Maybe he has one, but for all we know,

149
00:08:54,575 --> 00:08:56,285
he could be a criminal or a scammer!

150
00:08:56,369 --> 00:08:58,287
If he does have a child,
I bet he's hideous

151
00:08:58,371 --> 00:09:00,164
because I’ve never seen
a single picture of him in the shop.

152
00:09:00,915 --> 00:09:02,083
- [chuckles]
- [scoffs]

153
00:09:03,668 --> 00:09:05,795
[music concudes]

154
00:09:05,878 --> 00:09:07,046
[Cita sighs]

155
00:09:12,343 --> 00:09:14,887
Well, thanks for the gossip, and…

156
00:09:15,471 --> 00:09:16,973
I think I'm good.

157
00:09:17,056 --> 00:09:18,307
I no longer need a suit.

158
00:09:18,391 --> 00:09:19,809
- So…
- Oh, no…

159
00:09:19,892 --> 00:09:22,853
Hold on. Do you need a pillowcase?
I can definitely make one for you.

160
00:09:22,937 --> 00:09:24,188
Or perhaps, a curtain?

161
00:09:24,272 --> 00:09:25,606
A cover for your fridge?

162
00:09:25,690 --> 00:09:27,400
Clothes for a statue? Children's clothes?

163
00:09:27,483 --> 00:09:29,151
Clothes for your dog, your cat,
or perhaps, a bird?

164
00:09:29,235 --> 00:09:31,445
- Clothes for the dead? You name it.
- Excuse me.

165
00:09:31,529 --> 00:09:33,698
Get out of my way
before I smash your face in.

166
00:09:33,781 --> 00:09:34,740
- Excuse me.
- [Emerson] Oh?

167
00:09:37,702 --> 00:09:38,995
Oh…

168
00:09:39,078 --> 00:09:41,414
I see you've met Emerson.

169
00:09:41,497 --> 00:09:43,082
He works for your father.

170
00:09:43,165 --> 00:09:44,333
[Atoy] Hmm.

171
00:09:44,417 --> 00:09:45,585
[funky music playing]

172
00:09:45,668 --> 00:09:47,378
[stammering]

173
00:09:48,671 --> 00:09:50,256
That was you?

174
00:09:50,339 --> 00:09:52,842
[gasps] You're Sir Delfin's son?

175
00:09:52,925 --> 00:09:54,051
[Atoy scoffs]

176
00:09:54,635 --> 00:09:55,595
[Emerson] For real?

177
00:09:56,387 --> 00:09:57,888
Ever since?

178
00:09:57,972 --> 00:09:59,557
[snickering]

179
00:09:59,640 --> 00:10:01,267
I didn't know that was you!

180
00:10:01,350 --> 00:10:03,477
I didn't know that was you. [snickering]

181
00:10:03,561 --> 00:10:07,356
You should have told me sooner. [chuckles]

182
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:09,400
- I'm so glad to meet you, sir.
- Yes, it's me.

183
00:10:09,483 --> 00:10:11,902
- [chuckles]
- Well, um… [stammering]

184
00:10:11,986 --> 00:10:13,446
You don't look like a criminal at all.

185
00:10:13,529 --> 00:10:14,947
- Really?
- Yes!

186
00:10:15,031 --> 00:10:16,115
Also, you don't look like a scammer!

187
00:10:16,198 --> 00:10:20,411
You look like um… a soldier.

188
00:10:20,494 --> 00:10:22,872
- You even look like a model.
- [magical twinkle]

189
00:10:22,955 --> 00:10:26,417
You're like, um… Also, the way you act…

190
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:27,793
You look like a nice nice guy.

191
00:10:27,877 --> 00:10:29,920
Your beard also looks good on you.

192
00:10:30,004 --> 00:10:31,547
- Are you sure about that?
- Yes!

193
00:10:31,631 --> 00:10:34,342
Piolo and Dingdong don't stand
a chance against you!

194
00:10:34,425 --> 00:10:36,260
Right? I mean it.

195
00:10:36,344 --> 00:10:38,888
[humming]

196
00:10:38,971 --> 00:10:40,473
You look good!

197
00:10:40,556 --> 00:10:41,557
You look awesome!

198
00:10:41,641 --> 00:10:43,601
You should have told me sooner. [titters]

199
00:10:43,684 --> 00:10:45,561
I didn't know.

200
00:10:45,645 --> 00:10:47,313
It's fine.

201
00:10:47,813 --> 00:10:50,733
Anyway, you're better off
buying some barbecue.

202
00:10:50,816 --> 00:10:52,610
- I need 20 of them.
- Sure thing! Barbecue?

203
00:10:52,693 --> 00:10:54,320
Barbecue! No problem, I'll even add
some chicken intestines for you.

204
00:10:54,403 --> 00:10:55,529
Also, maybe some drinks.

205
00:10:55,613 --> 00:10:57,657
- Sounds good.
- There's a milk tea shop nearby.

206
00:10:57,740 --> 00:10:59,033
- Milk tea? [chuckles]
- Yes!

207
00:10:59,116 --> 00:11:00,701
Say less! I'll go get you some. Okay.

208
00:11:00,785 --> 00:11:04,538
You should stop by a rice store
and pick up about 2 kilos of rice as well!

209
00:11:04,622 --> 00:11:05,790
Two kilos? No problem. It's on me.

210
00:11:05,873 --> 00:11:07,625
Consider it my welcome gift, sir.

211
00:11:07,708 --> 00:11:09,043
- Approve! Thank you!
- Sounds good.

212
00:11:09,126 --> 00:11:10,127
Thank you!

213
00:11:10,211 --> 00:11:11,128
[playful music]

214
00:11:12,004 --> 00:11:13,881
- Something looks off…
- Oh.

215
00:11:13,964 --> 00:11:15,257
What was his name again? Emerson?

216
00:11:15,341 --> 00:11:16,509
Emerson.

217
00:11:16,592 --> 00:11:18,386
- I have to go. You can go inside.
- Got it.

218
00:11:18,469 --> 00:11:19,595
Your dad is still not around as well.

219
00:11:19,678 --> 00:11:20,638
Bye.

220
00:11:20,721 --> 00:11:24,100
[funky music continues]

221
00:11:27,019 --> 00:11:30,272
- [chiming]
- [music concludes]

222
00:11:37,071 --> 00:11:40,199
[crtitters chittering]

223
00:11:41,325 --> 00:11:42,535
What is this doing here?

224
00:11:44,161 --> 00:11:45,246
[sighs]

225
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:52,336
- [clatters]
- [chimes]

226
00:11:57,133 --> 00:11:58,592
[somber music]

227
00:12:00,511 --> 00:12:02,930
Who gave you the right to touch my stuff?

228
00:12:03,431 --> 00:12:06,016
[clears throat] Well, I'm just tidying up.

229
00:12:10,813 --> 00:12:12,731
[somber music playing]

230
00:12:12,815 --> 00:12:13,649
So now,

231
00:12:14,859 --> 00:12:17,611
you finally appreciate
what’s in this house?

232
00:12:25,828 --> 00:12:27,913
You’ve been away for ten years,

233
00:12:28,581 --> 00:12:32,460
and I never heard a word from you.

234
00:12:33,377 --> 00:12:36,547
Cita is lucky that
you never lost contact with her.

235
00:12:37,631 --> 00:12:38,966
But as for me…

236
00:12:39,717 --> 00:12:41,302
Most of the time…

237
00:12:41,927 --> 00:12:43,137
I didn't even know
you were already in Mindanao.

238
00:12:43,846 --> 00:12:46,056
No one asked you to look for me.

239
00:12:47,975 --> 00:12:52,104
You told me yourself
not to come back, remember?

240
00:12:52,730 --> 00:12:55,316
So why did you return? Huh?

241
00:12:55,399 --> 00:12:58,903
[somber music continues]

242
00:13:05,910 --> 00:13:07,953
Atoy, I left my glasses.

243
00:13:08,037 --> 00:13:11,999
[tense music playing]

244
00:13:14,877 --> 00:13:16,629
Are you two all right?

245
00:13:17,254 --> 00:13:21,133
Cita, you should talk to Atoy.

246
00:13:22,009 --> 00:13:24,345
He's been so arrogant
ever since he got here,

247
00:13:25,804 --> 00:13:28,557
and he even took it out on my mannequin!

248
00:13:29,600 --> 00:13:30,809
My bad.

249
00:13:30,893 --> 00:13:31,810
[scoffs]

250
00:13:31,894 --> 00:13:33,687
To hell with your mannequin.

251
00:13:34,813 --> 00:13:36,982
You can marry it for all I care.

252
00:13:37,066 --> 00:13:38,526
What in the world are you talking about?!

253
00:13:38,609 --> 00:13:39,693
Um… Delfin?

254
00:13:39,777 --> 00:13:43,072
I think Atoy
had no bad intentions whatsoever.

255
00:13:43,155 --> 00:13:44,698
I don't need that!

256
00:13:44,782 --> 00:13:46,283
What do you want?

257
00:13:47,201 --> 00:13:48,452
To show you resentment?

258
00:13:48,536 --> 00:13:49,912
[scoffs]

259
00:13:49,995 --> 00:13:50,996
I have a lot of those.

260
00:13:51,080 --> 00:13:53,165
If only your mom were still alive,

261
00:13:55,209 --> 00:13:57,127
she wouldn't be pleased
with what you're doing.

262
00:13:57,211 --> 00:14:01,840
I can say the exact same thing about you.

263
00:14:02,341 --> 00:14:03,551
It's a tie!

264
00:14:03,634 --> 00:14:06,845
[somber music playing]

265
00:14:12,768 --> 00:14:13,894
Hey!

266
00:14:13,978 --> 00:14:15,437
You better follow Atoy upstairs.

267
00:14:17,022 --> 00:14:20,192
And why should I?
It's not like he's running away.

268
00:14:20,276 --> 00:14:22,236
Well, do you want that to happen again?

269
00:14:22,736 --> 00:14:24,321
You've only got each other now!

270
00:14:24,405 --> 00:14:28,200
Do you think Jullie will be happy
seeing you two like this?

271
00:14:28,284 --> 00:14:30,327
Go comfort him yourself then!

272
00:14:30,411 --> 00:14:31,912
Why me? Huh?

273
00:14:32,496 --> 00:14:33,622
Why me?

274
00:14:34,290 --> 00:14:35,541
Who did he run away from?

275
00:14:36,041 --> 00:14:38,085
The economy is already terrible.

276
00:14:38,168 --> 00:14:40,170
This is no time to make things even worse!

277
00:14:40,254 --> 00:14:43,007
[sentimental music playing]

278
00:14:47,219 --> 00:14:54,059
[sentimental music continues]

279
00:15:15,039 --> 00:15:17,207
[birds chirping]

280
00:15:19,585 --> 00:15:24,173
[coughing]

281
00:15:28,844 --> 00:15:30,638
- Mom.
- Hmm?

282
00:15:30,721 --> 00:15:32,556
Would you like some snacks?

283
00:15:34,433 --> 00:15:38,270
There's a newly-opened burger joint
down the street.

284
00:15:38,354 --> 00:15:39,229
My treat.

285
00:15:39,313 --> 00:15:40,147
[chuckles]

286
00:15:40,230 --> 00:15:41,315
[gasps]

287
00:15:41,398 --> 00:15:43,817
Have you already told your dad?

288
00:15:45,069 --> 00:15:47,613
Let's meet him there, okay?

289
00:15:47,696 --> 00:15:49,073
Um…

290
00:15:49,573 --> 00:15:53,327
Well, the burger
is only buy one, get one free.

291
00:15:53,410 --> 00:15:58,290
I don't have enough money to treat Dad.

292
00:15:58,374 --> 00:16:05,130
Dear, why do you seem so distant
with your dad these days?

293
00:16:06,423 --> 00:16:08,592
You were never like this before.

294
00:16:09,593 --> 00:16:12,763
You two used to be close before.

295
00:16:14,348 --> 00:16:16,684
What have I ever done to you, huh?

296
00:16:17,309 --> 00:16:18,852
- Mom…
- Hmm?

297
00:16:18,936 --> 00:16:24,441
What if I told you that Dad
did something terrible to us?

298
00:16:27,861 --> 00:16:29,071
[coughs]

299
00:16:29,905 --> 00:16:32,908
[sighs]

300
00:16:32,992 --> 00:16:34,034
Dear…

301
00:16:35,661 --> 00:16:38,080
your dad is nowhere near perfect.

302
00:16:40,040 --> 00:16:42,209
The same also goes for me.

303
00:16:43,127 --> 00:16:46,630
[sighs] Regardless of what he has done,

304
00:16:48,424 --> 00:16:51,218
I will always love him.

305
00:16:53,429 --> 00:16:56,765
I am also sure your dad
loves you very much. [gasps]

306
00:17:01,603 --> 00:17:04,898
I’m sure it hurts your dad
that you’re giving him the cold shoulder.

307
00:17:04,982 --> 00:17:05,816
[gasps]

308
00:17:07,401 --> 00:17:12,156
And it hurts me even more
because I know he's hurt.

309
00:17:12,239 --> 00:17:14,074
[sobs]

310
00:17:15,701 --> 00:17:17,911
If possible… [sobs]

311
00:17:19,455 --> 00:17:22,458
…please be patient with your dad, okay?

312
00:17:22,541 --> 00:17:23,584
[sobs]

313
00:17:25,586 --> 00:17:29,256
Because I'm sure this isn't easy for him.

314
00:17:29,339 --> 00:17:30,507
[sobs]

315
00:17:30,591 --> 00:17:31,800
All right, Atoy?

316
00:17:31,884 --> 00:17:33,302
[sobbing]

317
00:17:33,385 --> 00:17:35,971
Hmm?

318
00:17:36,638 --> 00:17:39,641
[coughing]

319
00:17:39,725 --> 00:17:41,977
[coughs]

320
00:17:42,061 --> 00:17:43,479
Oh, Atoy.

321
00:17:43,562 --> 00:17:44,605
Father.

322
00:17:44,688 --> 00:17:46,940
Mel told me you've been here
for quite some time now.

323
00:17:47,941 --> 00:17:49,568
Yes, um…

324
00:17:50,861 --> 00:17:53,781
I just really miss Mom.

325
00:17:54,823 --> 00:17:58,368
She would always bring me here
back when she still could.

326
00:17:59,411 --> 00:18:00,496
I see, um…

327
00:18:00,579 --> 00:18:02,956
Do you feel her presence here?

328
00:18:04,041 --> 00:18:05,417
I do, even more than at home.

329
00:18:06,168 --> 00:18:08,170
That’s why I enjoy staying here.

330
00:18:09,171 --> 00:18:13,926
You’re welcome to stay,
but the church is closing.

331
00:18:14,426 --> 00:18:17,262
The staff will be polishing the floor.

332
00:18:17,888 --> 00:18:19,807
We’ll also be closing early

333
00:18:19,890 --> 00:18:22,518
because there’s ballroom dancing
in the barangay later,

334
00:18:22,601 --> 00:18:24,186
and all of us will be attending.

335
00:18:24,269 --> 00:18:26,605
[sentimental music playing]

336
00:18:26,688 --> 00:18:27,523
I see.

337
00:18:28,107 --> 00:18:29,817
Anyway, do you want to come with us?

338
00:18:30,317 --> 00:18:31,652
No need.

339
00:18:32,611 --> 00:18:33,821
Let me accompany you outside.

340
00:18:33,904 --> 00:18:34,905
All right, Father.

341
00:18:38,492 --> 00:18:41,495
Sir, I'm really sorry
for the inconvenience.

342
00:18:41,578 --> 00:18:42,412
It's fine.

343
00:18:42,496 --> 00:18:44,957
[mysterious music playing]

344
00:18:45,040 --> 00:18:47,334
[vacuum whirring]

345
00:18:56,635 --> 00:18:57,678
[priest] A-Atoy.

346
00:18:58,470 --> 00:19:01,306
Please take care,
and send my regards to your father.

347
00:19:10,691 --> 00:19:15,863
[mysterious music continues]

348
00:19:33,505 --> 00:19:34,965
[boy] You still owe me money!

349
00:19:35,048 --> 00:19:36,758
[vehicle honking in distance]

350
00:19:36,842 --> 00:19:38,927
[Emerson] Here you go, Mr. Chan.

351
00:19:39,011 --> 00:19:40,929
This suit will fit you perfectly.

352
00:19:41,013 --> 00:19:42,806
I'm sure you'll love it. [cackles]

353
00:19:42,890 --> 00:19:44,349
Thank you, Emerson.

354
00:19:44,433 --> 00:19:45,267
Why are you hiding?

355
00:19:45,350 --> 00:19:47,227
Mom's coworker is right over there!

356
00:19:47,311 --> 00:19:48,270
I can't be seen here.

357
00:19:48,353 --> 00:19:50,439
I'm sure they'll tell my mom
I went to the computer shop!

358
00:19:50,522 --> 00:19:52,524
[indistinct chatter]

359
00:19:52,608 --> 00:19:55,777
Anyway, Mr. Chan, for your son’s wedding,

360
00:19:55,861 --> 00:19:57,779
you can reach out to me to have
the groomsmen’s suits tailored.

361
00:19:57,863 --> 00:19:58,739
My prices are more affordable,

362
00:19:58,822 --> 00:20:00,532
and Sir Delfin won’t be able
to handle it anyway.

363
00:20:01,033 --> 00:20:02,910
How does that sound? You got it.

364
00:20:02,993 --> 00:20:05,370
- Thank you! Thank you so much.
- Huh?

365
00:20:05,454 --> 00:20:06,663
Thank you.

366
00:20:06,747 --> 00:20:11,877
[gibbering]

367
00:20:11,960 --> 00:20:14,755
All right! Take care, Mr. Chan!

368
00:20:14,838 --> 00:20:16,715
[gibbering]

369
00:20:16,798 --> 00:20:19,092
[mumbles]

370
00:20:19,176 --> 00:20:22,137
[snickering]

371
00:20:22,221 --> 00:20:24,014
- Brother!
- How are you doing?

372
00:20:24,097 --> 00:20:25,599
I'm good. [inhales]

373
00:20:25,682 --> 00:20:28,685
What are you doing here?

374
00:20:28,769 --> 00:20:30,854
What brings you here?
This isn't the way to your house.

375
00:20:30,938 --> 00:20:33,023
I know, and I think I'm lost.
I don't even know where I am.

376
00:20:33,106 --> 00:20:36,235
Oh, looks like we've stumbled
onto Traitor's Alley.

377
00:20:36,318 --> 00:20:38,987
- I'm not sure if this is the place.
- [chuckles] For real?"

378
00:20:39,571 --> 00:20:41,865
Are you for real? Come on, lighten up.

379
00:20:41,949 --> 00:20:44,409
I'm just pulling your leg. [mumbles]

380
00:20:44,493 --> 00:20:47,371
Anyway, did you receive
all the things I bought for you?

381
00:20:47,454 --> 00:20:48,413
I bought a lot just for you.

382
00:20:48,497 --> 00:20:49,790
Yes, I even gave it to your father.

383
00:20:49,873 --> 00:20:51,124
You must be referring
to your bribe as well.

384
00:20:51,208 --> 00:20:52,542
[quirky music]

385
00:20:52,626 --> 00:20:53,710
Oh no, no.

386
00:20:53,794 --> 00:20:56,213
- It was okay. I liked it.
- No, it's not what you think.

387
00:20:56,296 --> 00:20:57,339
That wasn't a bribe at all.

388
00:20:57,923 --> 00:20:59,633
That was my welcome gift for you.

389
00:20:59,716 --> 00:21:00,801
That, and also…

390
00:21:01,301 --> 00:21:03,595
Also, brother, if possible, please
don't tell your dad about this.

391
00:21:03,679 --> 00:21:04,596
[inhales]

392
00:21:04,680 --> 00:21:07,307
But if you do, that's fine too. It's okay.

393
00:21:07,391 --> 00:21:09,351
It's easy to forget that. [chuckles]

394
00:21:09,434 --> 00:21:12,437
So you want me to forget
that you went behind my father's back

395
00:21:12,521 --> 00:21:14,439
when you mistook me for a customer?

396
00:21:14,523 --> 00:21:16,441
- That is easy.
- No, no, it's not what you think!

397
00:21:16,525 --> 00:21:17,526
- That's not it!
- Should I tell him then?

398
00:21:17,609 --> 00:21:18,902
No, no, no, don't.

399
00:21:18,986 --> 00:21:20,445
Please don't tell him.
It's not what you think.

400
00:21:20,529 --> 00:21:22,364
You obviously misinter…

401
00:21:23,031 --> 00:21:26,326
[stammering] Interpreted…

402
00:21:26,410 --> 00:21:28,078
You don't get it, okay?

403
00:21:28,161 --> 00:21:30,247
You took our conversation the wrong way.

404
00:21:30,330 --> 00:21:34,042
Um, anyway, I just
don't want things to… um…

405
00:21:34,126 --> 00:21:35,502
- Atoy, it's like this…
- Hmm?

406
00:21:36,336 --> 00:21:38,588
Bro, I don't want to lose my job.

407
00:21:38,672 --> 00:21:42,676
Life's tough enough supporting
my siblings in the province,

408
00:21:42,759 --> 00:21:47,097
so please… [inhales]
…just let this one pass.

409
00:21:47,180 --> 00:21:48,473
Like that…

410
00:21:48,557 --> 00:21:49,975
Please don't say a word.

411
00:21:50,058 --> 00:21:51,351
- Fine.
- Okay?

412
00:21:51,435 --> 00:21:52,477
- You take care now.
- All right.

413
00:21:52,561 --> 00:21:54,146
Thank you, thank you.

414
00:21:54,229 --> 00:21:55,647
All right. [inhales]

415
00:21:55,731 --> 00:21:56,815
Unbelievable.

416
00:21:57,691 --> 00:21:59,067
You amaze me, sir!

417
00:21:59,568 --> 00:22:03,739
[somber music playing]

418
00:22:40,192 --> 00:22:41,860
Don't tell me how to do my job.

419
00:22:41,943 --> 00:22:43,487
But that is exactly what you need.

420
00:22:43,570 --> 00:22:44,446
No!

421
00:22:47,783 --> 00:22:49,743
I may not be a master cutter,

422
00:22:51,078 --> 00:22:53,330
but I know for a fact
that you're doing it wrong.

423
00:22:54,414 --> 00:22:56,291
How will you fix your mistakes

424
00:22:56,792 --> 00:22:58,794
if you don't carefully mend them?

425
00:22:58,877 --> 00:23:02,714
[tense music]

426
00:23:02,798 --> 00:23:05,300
How can I fix my mistakes
if you don't say anything?

427
00:23:05,884 --> 00:23:07,427
I'm not a mind-reader!

428
00:23:10,263 --> 00:23:11,306
[mutters]

429
00:23:12,557 --> 00:23:13,391
Also, you know what?

430
00:23:14,726 --> 00:23:17,854
Since your mother got sick,
you've changed.

431
00:23:18,772 --> 00:23:19,689
[scoffs]

432
00:23:20,565 --> 00:23:24,402
I honestly don't know
where I went wrong with you.

433
00:23:25,904 --> 00:23:27,906
- Really now?
- Is it…

434
00:23:27,989 --> 00:23:30,450
because I didn't
want you to join the army?

435
00:23:30,951 --> 00:23:32,202
[scoffs]

436
00:23:32,786 --> 00:23:34,788
That's such a shallow reason

437
00:23:34,871 --> 00:23:37,457
for you to ignore me all these years!

438
00:23:37,958 --> 00:23:39,292
So you want a deeper reason?

439
00:23:39,960 --> 00:23:43,672
One deeper reason that no
sewing machine could ever mend?

440
00:23:46,508 --> 00:23:48,385
Maybe, the only solution is a miracle.

441
00:23:50,053 --> 00:23:53,223
[dramatic music playing]

442
00:24:13,160 --> 00:24:18,123
[suspenseful music playing]

443
00:24:28,633 --> 00:24:34,806
[suspenseful music continues]

444
00:24:54,284 --> 00:24:56,161
Where are you going, Saint Anthony?

445
00:24:56,828 --> 00:25:00,999
[suspenseful music continues]

446
00:25:04,878 --> 00:25:11,051
[slurred humming]

447
00:25:11,134 --> 00:25:12,969
[music concludes]

448
00:25:13,053 --> 00:25:15,263
[crickets chirping in distance]

449
00:25:39,287 --> 00:25:43,500
[pensive music playing]

450
00:25:49,256 --> 00:25:50,257
[man] Ma'am Julie,

451
00:25:50,340 --> 00:25:52,592
we'll pin your family picture
on the bulletin board.

452
00:25:52,676 --> 00:25:55,262
No problem. Also, send me a copy, okay?

453
00:25:55,345 --> 00:25:57,514
- All right.
- Have it delivered to our house, okay?

454
00:25:58,265 --> 00:25:59,516
- I have to go.
- Got it.

455
00:26:01,059 --> 00:26:07,274
[pensive music continues]

456
00:26:31,089 --> 00:26:32,799
Let us pray.

457
00:26:41,766 --> 00:26:46,396
Saint Anthony, I pray
that my husband and son,

458
00:26:47,939 --> 00:26:50,734
even if they don’t understand each other,

459
00:26:51,901 --> 00:26:55,030
I hope they can find
their way back to each other.

460
00:26:56,239 --> 00:26:58,700
That's a tough one.

461
00:27:00,327 --> 00:27:01,911
Even when I’m gone,

462
00:27:03,872 --> 00:27:09,002
I hope they will come here together
and turn to you with all their hearts.

463
00:27:09,878 --> 00:27:12,839
Julie, don’t speak like that.

464
00:27:12,922 --> 00:27:14,799
That’s exactly why we’re going
to have you treated.

465
00:27:17,385 --> 00:27:19,929
Mom, you look pale.

466
00:27:20,513 --> 00:27:22,432
You also get exhausted really quickly.

467
00:27:22,515 --> 00:27:25,101
You shouldn't have insisted
on coming here.

468
00:27:26,353 --> 00:27:28,772
If I do not force
the two of you to come here,

469
00:27:28,855 --> 00:27:31,816
you and your father wouldn't
be here with me right now.

470
00:27:36,321 --> 00:27:40,033
[tense music]

471
00:27:40,116 --> 00:27:41,242
- Mom?
- Julie?

472
00:27:41,326 --> 00:27:42,369
- Mom!
- Julie!

473
00:27:42,452 --> 00:27:43,286
- Mom! Mom!
- Julie!

474
00:27:43,370 --> 00:27:44,704
- Mom?
- I got it, I got it!

475
00:27:44,788 --> 00:27:45,622
I'll handle this.

476
00:27:45,705 --> 00:27:46,873
- Leave it to me!
- [gasps]

477
00:27:47,707 --> 00:27:49,417
Julie! Julie!

478
00:27:49,501 --> 00:27:53,129
[brooding music playing]

479
00:28:21,741 --> 00:28:23,493
[music concludes]

480
00:28:24,786 --> 00:28:27,205
Is Atoy still sleeping?

481
00:28:28,915 --> 00:28:30,041
How was last night?

482
00:28:30,125 --> 00:28:31,709
Are things between you two good now?

483
00:28:33,753 --> 00:28:36,047
Yes, but I don't even know anymore.

484
00:28:36,923 --> 00:28:38,258
I can't quite figure him out.

485
00:28:38,341 --> 00:28:41,177
[somber music]

486
00:28:41,261 --> 00:28:43,763
Just give it a little more time.

487
00:28:43,847 --> 00:28:45,849
I'll talk to him myself.

488
00:28:48,435 --> 00:28:53,857
Mom, there's this group project
in science that we have to work on.

489
00:28:54,441 --> 00:28:56,901
I need one hundred pesos
for my contribution.

490
00:28:57,485 --> 00:28:59,612
You've had countless
school projects lately!

491
00:29:00,321 --> 00:29:01,489
Anyway,

492
00:29:02,699 --> 00:29:06,077
I noticed that Mr. Chan has never
availed any of our services again.

493
00:29:07,454 --> 00:29:09,289
It's been nearly a month.

494
00:29:10,415 --> 00:29:12,375
Did he ever tell you why?

495
00:29:13,001 --> 00:29:15,670
Emerson was the last person he spoke to.

496
00:29:15,754 --> 00:29:17,505
Something unexpected must have happened.

497
00:29:18,006 --> 00:29:21,050
[Emerson] Anyway, Mr. Chan,
for your son’s wedding,

498
00:29:21,134 --> 00:29:23,261
you can reach out to me
to have the groomsmen’s suits tailored.

499
00:29:23,344 --> 00:29:24,262
My prices are more affordable,

500
00:29:24,345 --> 00:29:26,014
and Sir Delfin won’t be able
to handle it anyway.

501
00:29:26,514 --> 00:29:28,183
- How does that sound?
- Mom.

502
00:29:28,725 --> 00:29:33,354
Is Mr. Chan the old man
with the rotten teeth?

503
00:29:33,438 --> 00:29:35,231
The man with thick glasses on?

504
00:29:36,441 --> 00:29:38,276
Yes, that's him. Why do you ask?

505
00:29:39,068 --> 00:29:41,070
I saw him and Emerson last night.

506
00:29:41,154 --> 00:29:43,072
Emerson even handed him his order

507
00:29:43,656 --> 00:29:47,577
and said that next time,
Mr. Chan should go to him

508
00:29:47,660 --> 00:29:49,913
because you’re no longer capable.

509
00:29:49,996 --> 00:29:51,080
[Cita] What?

510
00:29:51,164 --> 00:29:53,333
Have you already fallen ill, Sir Delfin?

511
00:29:53,416 --> 00:29:55,585
I'm stronger than a horse, Karla!

512
00:29:55,668 --> 00:29:58,004
Looks like I've got a traitor
to deal with.

513
00:29:58,713 --> 00:29:59,547
Delfin!

514
00:29:59,631 --> 00:30:02,967
[tense music playing]

515
00:30:03,051 --> 00:30:03,885
Oh!

516
00:30:03,968 --> 00:30:06,179
[music concludes]

517
00:30:08,223 --> 00:30:09,390
[man] Good morning, Father.

518
00:30:09,974 --> 00:30:11,768
Just take all the dry ones.

519
00:30:12,352 --> 00:30:14,020
[man] Hmm. Got it.

520
00:30:19,901 --> 00:30:21,027
[inquisitive music playing]

521
00:30:21,110 --> 00:30:22,695
- Mel.
- [Mel] Yes?

522
00:30:23,196 --> 00:30:25,240
Did someone move the Saint Anthony statue?

523
00:30:25,824 --> 00:30:26,991
[tense music]

524
00:30:27,075 --> 00:30:28,284
No, Father.

525
00:30:28,368 --> 00:30:30,411
Also, we just got inside.

526
00:30:30,495 --> 00:30:33,623
Then why is the statue not here?

527
00:30:33,706 --> 00:30:35,041
Where is it?

528
00:30:36,835 --> 00:30:39,003
[intense music playing]

529
00:30:46,970 --> 00:30:47,846
Who was abducted?

530
00:30:47,929 --> 00:30:49,013
Nobody!

531
00:30:49,097 --> 00:30:50,765
[woman] The statue is missing.

532
00:30:50,849 --> 00:30:53,518
Someone stole the Saint Anthony
of Padua statue!

533
00:30:53,601 --> 00:30:55,603
[crowd] Bring Saint Anthony back!

534
00:30:55,687 --> 00:30:56,521
[gasping]

535
00:30:56,604 --> 00:30:59,983
You know, if there's anyone
who truly cares about Saint Anthony,

536
00:31:00,066 --> 00:31:00,900
it's me!

537
00:31:00,984 --> 00:31:02,277
Hello.

538
00:31:02,360 --> 00:31:04,153
At last, we meet.

539
00:31:04,237 --> 00:31:06,865
UP NEXT

540
00:31:11,828 --> 00:31:12,662
[Atoy] <i>Hey!</i>

541
00:31:20,086 --> 00:31:23,339
Subtitle translation by:
Inocencio Cañete Raman Jr.
